title: What channel is Kansas City Royals-Houston Astros on? TV, live stream for ALDS Game 1
text:
Defending AL champ Kansas City begins its 2015 postseason by hosting Houston tonight in Game 1 of a best-of-5 American League Division Series.
Yordano Ventura will take the mound for Kansas City while Collin McHugh gets the nod for Houston.
The game starts at 7:30 p.m. and will be televised by Fox Sports 1.
Here's how to see Fox Sports 1 in Central New York:
Time Warner: Channel 400 (SD & HD) Verizon Fios: Channel 583 (HD) and 83 (SD) DirectTV: Channel 219 (SD & HD) Dish Network: Channel 150 (SD &HD) New Visions: Channel 768 (HD) and 83 (SD) You can also watch online or through tablets and mobile devices using FOX Sports GO .
